DAMATURU – A new Police Commissioner has been posted to Yobe Police Command Damaturu. He is CP Haruna G. Garba who stands as the 31st Commissioner of Police since the creation of Yobe State. He took over from the former Commissioner of Police, Yahaya Sahabo Abubakar who has now been elevated to the rank of AIG. The Commissioner of Police Haruna G Garba hails from Kogi State and holds a Bachelor of Science Degree in Political Science and Administration from the University of Maiduguri and MSc. International Relations from the University of Uyo, Akwa-Ibom State. Buni Signs Yobe 2022 Appropriation Bill Into Law Group Meets To Improve Development In Yobe Communities He was appointed into the Nigeria Police Force as a cadet Assistant Superintendent of Police on 3rd March 1990. He has held Tactical and Strategic leadership positions in various departments of the Force across the Country.Until his deployment as the Commissioner of Police Yobe State Police Command, he was the Deputy Commissioner of Police in charge of State CID in Yobe State. The new Police Commissioner in Yobe possesses vast experience in law enforcement, public order management and public safety, Intellectual property crime, Fundamental human rights, Crime Control and Community Policing as contained in a statement signed by ASP Dungus Abdulkarim, Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) Yobe Police Command. “To this end, the Command wishes to use this medium to solicit the support of the members of the public to the new Commissioner of Police to enable him to serve you better in the course of providing security and public safety”.